BSE UPDATE 2003 (02)
********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
This bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) update includes, in article
[1], a "BSE cases update", which summarises in table form all BSE cases
reported, by country, until the date of posting. As from now, further cases
of BSE in infected countries will, generally, no longer be reported
separately but will be incorporated into the table, to be included as
article [1] in future updates. Detailed, separate reports on new BSE cases
will be published only when important information or new developments are
involved.
In these updates:
[1] BSE cases update, 07 Feb 2003
[2] WHO consumer information
[3] WHO concerns on continuing BSE risks
[4] BSE in Japan
[5] BSE in Spain
[6] SSC opinions on disposal of BSE-risk material
[7] BSE control in Israel
