[5]
Date: Tue, 28 Jan 2003
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: La Vanguardia (Spain) 28 Jan 2003 [in Spanish] [translated &
summarized by Mod.JW]

18 foci declared since the start of tests
-----------------------------------------
The agriculture department of Catalonia confirms 2 cases of BSE, one on 23
Jan 2003 in the Alt Urgell slaughterhouse, originating in Ribera de
Urgellet (Lleida), and the other today, 28 Jan 2003, from Banyoles
(Girona), where 23 cattle have been destroyed [later in the story it says
80 cows and 75 calves were destroyed in that herd. - Mod.JW]
These cases bring to 18 the total number of cattle affected by BSE in
Catalonia since 1 Jan 2001, when the European Union regulations for testing
entered into force: 6 in 2001, 10 in 2002, plus these 2.
